2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1234
AMENDME NT 1234A
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Roby
1 An Act to revise procedural requirements for provisions related to serving a
2 subpoena in a contested case.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 1-26-18 be AMENDED:
5 1-26-18. Opportunity shall be afforded to all parties to respond and present
6 evidence on issues of fact and argument on issues of law or policy. However, each Each
7 agency, upon the motion of any party, may dispose of any defense or claim:
8 (1) If the pleadings, depositions, answers to interrogatories, and admissions on file,
9 together with the affidavits, if any, show that there is no genuine issue as to any
10 material fact and a party is entitled to a judgment as a matter of law; or
11 (2) At the close of the evidence offered by the proponent of the defense or claim, if it
12 the agency determines that the evidence offered by the proponent of the defense
13 or claim is legally insufficient to sustain the defense or claim.
14 A party to a contested case proceeding may appear in person or by counsel, or
15 both, and may be present during the giving of all evidence,. The party or the party's
16 attorney of record may have reasonable opportunity to inspect all documentary evidence,
17 may examine and cross-examine witnesses, may present evidence in support of the
18 party's interest, and may have subpoenas issued issue subpoenas to compel attendance
19 of witnesses and production of evidence in on the party's behalf.
20 Section 2. That § 1-26-19.1 be AMENDED:
21 1-26-19.1. Each agency and the officers thereof any attorney of record or officer
22 of the agency charged with the duty to administer the laws of this the state and the rules
23 of the agency shall have power to administer may:
24 (1) Administer oaths as provided by chapter 18-3 and to subpoena; and
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1234A 2 1234
1 (2) Subpoena witnesses or interested parties to appear and give testimony and to
2 produce records, books, papers, and documents relating to any matters in
3 contested cases and likewise issue subpoenas for such purposes for persons
4 interested therein matter in a contested case, as provided by in § 15-6-45.
5 Unless otherwise provided by law, fees for witnesses shall be are as set forth in
6 chapter 19-5 and must be paid by the agency or party for whom the witness is
7 subpoenaed.
8 Failure of a person to obey the a subpoena issued pursuant to this chapter may be
9 punished as a contempt of court in the manner provided by chapter 21-34.
10 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 1-26:
11 Before a subpoena commanding the production of documentary evidence pursuant
12 to § 1-26-19.1 is served on the person to whom it is directed, a notice and copy of the
13 subpoena must be served on each party to the matter pending. The hearing examiner or
14 administrative law judge, upon motion made promptly and at or before the time specified
15 in the subpoena for compliance with the subpoena, may:
16 (1) Quash or modify the subpoena if it is unreasonable and oppressive; or
17 (2) Condition denial of the motion upon the advancement, by the person on whose
18 behalf the subpoena is issued, of the reasonable cost of producing the records,
19 books, papers, or documents.
